Others: The Oklahoma City Thunder won against the LA Clippers with a score of 116-98.
Amir Coffey led the Clippers with 26 points.
The Thunder forced 19 turnovers to the Clippers' 11.
The Thunder's core players, including Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and Jalen Williams, had a significant impact on the game.
The Thunder outrebounded the Clippers, but the large turnover disparity between the two teams contributed to the Thunder's win.
